Create a sideEffect type that automatically aggregates child (sub-table) fields to the parent record. This is a common ERP pattern: sum line amounts → header total.

Use case: When a WH In line is created/updated/deleted, automatically SUM(pe_wh_in_line_amount) → pe_wh_in_total_amount on the parent WH In header.

Design:
1. New sideEffect type in command DSL: "AGGREGATE"
```json
{
  "type": "AGGREGATE",
  "config": {
    "childModel": "pe_warehouse_in_line",
    "childField": "pe_wh_in_line_amount",
    "parentModel": "pe_warehouse_in",
    "parentField": "pe_wh_in_total_amount",
    "parentFk": "pe_wh_in_line_receipt_id",
    "function": "SUM"
  }
}
```

Implementation:
1. platform/src/main/java/com/auraboot/module/meta/command/sideeffect/AggregateSideEffect.java
```java
@Component
public class AggregateSideEffect implements SideEffectHandler {
    @Override
    public String getType() { return "AGGREGATE"; }

    @Override
    public void execute(SideEffectContext context) {
        Map<String, Object> config = context.getConfig();
        String childModel = (String) config.get("childModel");
        String childField = (String) config.get("childField");
        String parentModel = (String) config.get("parentModel");
        String parentField = (String) config.get("parentField");
        String parentFk = (String) config.get("parentFk");
        String function = (String) config.getOrDefault("function", "SUM");

        // Get parent ID from the current record
        Long parentId = resolveParentId(context, parentFk);
        if (parentId == null) return;

        // Query all child records
        List<Map<String, Object>> children = context.getDataAccessor()
            .query(childModel, Map.of(parentFk, parentId));

        // Aggregate
        BigDecimal result = children.stream()
            .map(child -> toBigDecimal(child.get(childField)))
            .reduce(BigDecimal.ZERO, BigDecimal::add);

        // Update parent
        context.getDataAccessor().update(parentModel, parentId,
            Map.of(parentField, result));
    }
}
```

2. Register in the sideEffect handler registry (find existing registration pattern).

3. Check existing sideEffect infrastructure:
- Look for SideEffectHandler interface or similar in platform/src/main/java/com/auraboot/module/meta/command/
- If no sideEffect handler system exists, create a minimal one

