- testEmptyChildren: no children → parent total = 0
- testNullFieldValues: some children have null amounts → treated as 0
- testUpdateTrigger: update a child amount → parent recalculated

Create a reusable Excel import framework for bulk data entry (materials, BOMs, resources, etc.).

Create:
1. platform/src/main/java/com/auraboot/module/meta/excel/ExcelImportService.java
```java
@Service
@RequiredArgsConstructor
public class ExcelImportService {
    private final DynamicEntityService entityService;
    private final MetaModelService modelService;
    private final MetaFieldService fieldService;

    /**
     * Import Excel file into a dynamic model.
     * Steps: parse → validate → preview → insert
     */
    public ExcelImportResult importExcel(String modelCode, InputStream excelStream, ImportOptions options) {
        // 1. Parse: Read headers + rows using Apache POI (already in classpath for Spring Boot)
        List<Map<String, Object>> rawRows = parseExcel(excelStream);

        // 2. Map: Convert column headers to field codes
        //    Match by displayName (zh-CN or en) or by field code
        List<MetaFieldDto> fields = fieldService.getFieldsByModel(modelCode);
        List<Map<String, Object>> mappedRows = mapColumnsToFields(rawRows, fields);

        // 3. Validate: Check required fields, data types, references
        List<ImportValidationError> errors = validate(mappedRows, fields);
        if (!errors.isEmpty() && !options.isSkipErrors()) {
            return ExcelImportResult.withErrors(errors, rawRows.size());
        }

        // 4. Insert valid rows via Command engine (respects all business rules)
        int successCount = 0;
        int errorCount = 0;
        for (Map<String, Object> row : mappedRows) {
            try {
                // Use command execution to create records
                entityService.create(modelCode, row);
                successCount++;
            } catch (Exception e) {
                errorCount++;
                if (!options.isSkipErrors()) throw e;
            }
        }

        return ExcelImportResult.success(successCount, errorCount, errors);
    }
}
```

